"Raisins, cherry cordials, banana esters on the nose. Nice deep maroon color. Dried fruit (cherries, figs, plums), some clove, and noticeable honey. Finishes sweet. Smooth and slightly velvety, and wamr on the throat. A bit on the sweet side but impressed by how it's so easy to drink."
"O: Overall a decent beer for when you are in the mood for a nice dark Belgian style.. Interesting, and new."
